T1  - Questions of Causation in the Path-Goal Theory of Leadership
AU  - Greene, Charles N.
Y1  - 1979/03/01
PY  - 1979
DA  - 1979/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255476
DO  - 10.5465/255476
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 22
EP  - 41
VL  - 22
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This paper reports results of two studies which investigated elements of the current (House  House & Mitchell, 1974) and initial (House, 1971) versions of the path-goal theory of leadership. The first constituted a replication and the second a longitudinal study which tested several assumptions about causation which underlie both versions of the theory. The findings largely supported the theory with the notable exception of the hypotheses concerning subordinate performance.
AB  - This paper reports results of two studies which investigated elements of the current (House  House & Mitchell, 1974) and initial (House, 1971) versions of the path-goal theory of leadership. The first constituted a replication and the second a longitudinal study which tested several assumptions about causation which underlie both versions of the theory. The findings largely supported the theory with the notable exception of the hypotheses concerning subordinate performance.
