TY  - JOUR
T1  - Forecasting Teller Window Demand with Exponential Smoothing
AU  - Berry, William L.
AU  - Mabert, Vincent A.
AU  - Marcus, Myles
Y1  - 1979/03/01
PY  - 1979
DA  - 1979/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255485
DO  - 10.5465/255485
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 129
EP  - 137
VL  - 22
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This paper demonstrates the use of exponential smoothing to forecast the total daily demand for teller window services in a bank. It describes (1) the procedures that were used to detect the underlying causes of systematic variation in teller window demand and (2) the use of an exponential smoothing model with seasonal factors that are not time dependent. Experimental results are presented which illustrate the improvement in forecasting performance obtained by using the nontime-dependent seasonal factors. The resulting forecasts provide a means of improving teller window staffing decisions.
AB  - This paper demonstrates the use of exponential smoothing to forecast the total daily demand for teller window services in a bank. It describes (1) the procedures that were used to detect the underlying causes of systematic variation in teller window demand and (2) the use of an exponential smoothing model with seasonal factors that are not time dependent. Experimental results are presented which illustrate the improvement in forecasting performance obtained by using the nontime-dependent seasonal factors. The resulting forecasts provide a means of improving teller window staffing decisions.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/255485
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/255485
Y2  - 2026/04/24
